<p>Last update 01/2022</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2><strong>What are cookies</strong></h2>

<p>Cookies are small files that our sites send to your computer or cell pho=
ne and are saved on these devices. They allow us to analyze web traffic and=
 thus optimize your Internet surfing.</p>

<p>Cookies also serve the site itself to recognize you and to find your per=
sonal preferences such as your location and language and your shopping cart=
.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2><strong>How to manage or delete cookies</strong></h2>

<p><br>
The way cookies work, as well as the options for restricting or blocking th=
em, can be adjusted by changing the settings of your Internet browser. Most=
 internet browsers are initially set up to accept cookies automatically, bu=
t you can change these settings to block cookies or to be notified whenever=
 cookies are sent to your device. There are several ways to manage cookies,=
 so please refer to your browser's instruction manual or help screen to see=
 how to adjust or change your browser settings. In fact, the user is allowe=
d to modify the default configuration and disable cookies (i.e. block them =
permanently) by setting the highest level of protection.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Below is the path to follow to manage cookies from the following browser=
s:</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Explorer: <u><a href=3D"http://windows.microsoft.com/it-it/windows7/bloc=
k-enable-or-allow-cookies" target=3D"_black">http://windows.microsoft.com/i=
t-it/windows7/block-enable-or-allow-cookies</a></u></p>

<p>Safari: <u><a href=3D"https://support.apple.com/it-it/HT201265" target=
=3D"_black">http://support.apple.com/kb/PH11913</a></u></p>

<p>Chrome: <u><a href=3D"https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=
=3Den-EN&amp;hlrm=3Dfr&amp;hlrm=3Den" target=3D"_black">https://support.goo=
gle.com/chrome/answer/95647?hl=3Dit-IT&amp;hlrm=3Dfr&amp;hlrm=3Den</a></u><=
/p>

<p>Firefox: &nbsp;<u><a href=3D"http://support.mozilla.org/it-IT/kb/enable-=
and-disable-cookies-website-preferences" target=3D"_black">http://support.m=
ozilla.org/it-IT/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences</a></u><=
/p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2><strong>Types and purposes of cookies use</strong></h2>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Navigation cookies</strong></p>

<p>From the first access these cookies allow the site to function properly =
and allow you to view content on your device by recognizing the <strong>lan=
guage </strong>and the market of the <strong>country from which you have ch=
osen to connect</strong>. If you are a registered user, they will allow us =
to recognize you and access the services offered in the dedicated areas. Na=
vigation cookies are<strong> technical cookies</strong> and are necessary f=
or the site to function.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Functional cookies</strong></p>

<p>These cookies make it possible, according to your request,<strong> to re=
cognise you on subsequent accesses </strong>so that you don't have to enter=
 your details each time you visit (for example: "Recognise me next time").<=
/p>

<p>If you have added items to your basket and closed the session without co=
mpleting the purchase and without deleting them, these cookies allow you to=
 continue shopping the next time you access the site (within a limited peri=
od) and find the items you selected.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Statistical cookies from </strong><b>Giannini Shop Online</b><st=
rong> and third parties</strong></p>

<p>These cookies are used to perform <strong>statistical analysis of how us=
ers navigate our site.</strong> We process the results of these analyses an=
onymously and solely for statistical purposes only if the service provider =
uses cookies in connection with the browser used or on other devices used t=
o browse the site. The site uses some third-party services that, quite inde=
pendently, install their own cookies:</p>

<p>- <u><a href=3D"https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=3Den">Google Anal=
itycs</a></u></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Social Network cookies</strong></p>

<p>These cookies are necessary to allow <strong>your social account</strong=
> to interact with our site. They are used, for example, to let you express=
 your appreciation and share it with your social friends. Social network co=
okies are not required for navigation.</p>

